OL,3,C'Cheers, drive!' - Why this bride took
OL,4,Ca bus to her wedding
OL,6,FAlex Harrison, Disability Wales'
OL,7,FDisability Equality Officer, says
OL,8,Fdisabled people often have to go
OL,9,Fwithout luxury on their wedding day,
OL,10,Fbut encounter many hurdles as a result.
OL,12,F"We see it constantly. Organising a
OL,13,Fwedding is stressful enough without
OL,14,Fall these extra barriers to work
OL,15,Fthrough. I think there needs to be
OL,16,Fmore understanding and I think
OL,17,Fsuppliers and the wedding industry, as
OL,18,Fa whole, need to realise that disabled
OL,19,Fpeople like to get married too."
